#. Tag: title
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "&vmguest; Clock Settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:12
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Keeping the correct time in a &vmguest; is one of the more difficult aspects "
"of virtualization. Keeping the correct time is especially important for "
"network applications and is also a prerequisite to do a live migration of a "
"&vmguest;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:25
#, no-c-format
msgid "Timekeeping on the &vmhost;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:26
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is strongly recommended to ensure the &vmhost; keeps the correct time as "
"well, for example, by using NTP (see <xref linkend=\"cha.netz.xntp\"/> for "
"more information)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:33
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kvm;: Using <systemitem>kvm_clock</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:35
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kvm; provides a paravirtualized clock which is currently supported by &sls; "
"10 SP3 and newer and RedHat Enterprise Linux 5.4 and newer via the "
"<systemitem>kvm_clock</systemitem> driver. It is strongly recommended to use "
"<systemitem>kvm_clock</systemitem> when available."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:42
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the following command inside a &vmguest; running Linux to check whether "
"the driver <systemitem>kvm_clock</systemitem> has been loaded:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:47
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.user;sudo dmesg | grep kvm-clock\n"
"[    0.000000] kvm-clock: cpu 0, msr 0:7d3a81, boot clock\n"
"[    0.000000] kvm-clock: cpu 0, msr 0:1206a81, primary cpu clock\n"
"[    0.012000] kvm-clock: cpu 1, msr 0:1306a81, secondary cpu clock\n"
"[    0.160082] Switching to clocksource kvm-clock"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:49
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To check which clock source is currently used, run the following command in "
"the &vmguest;. It should output <literal>kvm-clock</literal>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:54
#, no-c-format
msgid "cat /sys/devices/system/clocksource/clocksource0/current_clocksource"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>kvm-clock</literal> and NTP"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using <literal>kvm-clock</literal>, it is recommended to use NTP in the "
"&vmguest;, as well. Using NTP on the &vmhost; is also recommended."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:67
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other Timekeeping Methods"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:68
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The paravirtualized <literal>kvm-clock</literal> is currently not for "
"Windows* operating systems. For Windows*, use the <literal>Windows Time "
"Service Tools</literal> for time synchronization (see <link xlink:href="
"\"http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/cc773263%28WS.10%29.aspx\"></"
"link> for more information)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:90
#, no-c-format
msgid "&xen; Virtual Machine Clock Settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:92
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When booting, virtual machines get their initial clock time from their host. "
"After getting their initial clock time, fully virtual machines manage their "
"time independently from the host. Paravirtual machines manage clock time "
"according to their independent wallclock setting. If the independent "
"wallclock is enabled, the virtual machine manages its time independently and "
"does not synchronize with the host. If the independent wallclock is "
"disabled, the virtual machine periodically synchronizes its time with the "
"host clock."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"OES 2 NetWare virtual machines manage clock time independently after "
"booting. They do not synchronize with the host clock time."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a guest operating system is configured for NTP and the virtual machine's "
"independent wallclock setting is disabled, it will still periodically "
"synchronize its time with the host time. This dual type of configuration can "
"result in time drift between virtual machines that need to be synchronized. "
"To effectively use an external time source, such as NTP, for time "
"synchronization on a virtual machine, the virtual machine's independent "
"wallclock setting must be enabled (set to <command>1</command>). Otherwise, "
"it will continue to synchronize its time with its host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:123
#, no-c-format
msgid "Viewing the Independent Wallclock Setting"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:125
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Log in to the virtual machine’s operating system as <systemitem>root</"
"systemitem>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:131
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the virtual machine environment, enter"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:134
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>cat /proc/sys/xen/independent_wallclock</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:137
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>0</command> means that the virtual machine is getting its time from "
"the host and is not using independent wallclock."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:143
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>1</command> means that the virtual machine is using independent "
"wallclock and managing its time independently from the host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:154
#, no-c-format
msgid "Permanently Changing the Independent Wallclock Setting"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:156 vt_clocksettings.xml:193
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Log in to the virtual machine environment as <systemitem>root</systemitem>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:162
#, no-c-format
msgid "Edit the virtual machine’s <filename>/etc/sysctl.conf</filename> file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:168 vt_clocksettings.xml:209
#, no-c-format
msgid "Add or change the following entry:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:171 vt_clocksettings.xml:212
#, no-c-format
msgid "xen.independent_wallclock=1"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:172 vt_clocksettings.xml:203 vt_clocksettings.xml:213
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enter <command>1</command> to enable or <command>0</command> to disable the "
"wallclock setting."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:178
#, no-c-format
msgid "Save the file and reboot the virtual machine operating system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:181
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"While booting, a virtual machine gets its initial clock time from the host. "
"Then, if the wallclock setting is set to 1 in the <filename>sysctl.conf</"
"filename> file, it manages its clock time independently and does not "
"synchronize with the host clock time."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:191
#, no-c-format
msgid "Temporarily Changing the Independent Wallclock Setting"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:199
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enter the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:202
#, no-c-format
msgid "echo \"1\" &gt; /proc/sys/xen/independent_wallclock"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vt_clocksettings.xml:217
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Although the current status of the independent wallclock changes "
"immediately, its clock time might not be immediately synchronized. The "
"setting persists until the virtual machine reboots. Then, it gets its "
"initial clock time from the host and uses the independent wallclock "
"according to the setting specified in the <filename>sysctl.conf</filename> "
"file."
msgstr ""
